V<p>Wow, the summer has gone by incredibly fast!  And, uh, I keep forgetting to blog.  Sorry.  I will hopefully finish my security series relatively soon, and then I&#8217;ll have to move on to something new!  Suggestions are very welcome.</p>\u000a<p>Some filler:</p>\u000a<p>Right now, it is work week at the co-op I live in, which means that we all work on building/cleaning/etc. projects around the house.  I&#8217;m one of the house managers, which means that I get to organize the whole thing!  In particular, we are fixing parts of our 40+ year old deck that have begun to rot, and hopefully we will rebuild the stairs that we tore down last year.  I&#8217;ve also got the same room as I had last semester, and I&#8217;ve spiced it up a bit, such that it is more conducive to both entertaining people and just relaxing or working.  Spending time in it is now much more enjoyable!</p>\u000a<p>I am planning to take four classes next term:  6.046 (Design and Analysis of Algorithms), 6.882 (Planning and Decision-Making), 6.UAT (Preparation for Undergraduate Advanced Project), and 9.85 (Infant and Early Childhood Cognition).  I am particularly excited about 6.882, which is being taught be Leslie Kaelbling, who is a fantastic professor in machine learning, and whom I respect immensely.  I think that the techniques I will learn in this class will be very applicable to my research, which applies Bayesian statistics to cognitive science in order to create models of cognition.  Plus, it fulfills one of the CS requirements I need to graduate!  I love it when things work out that way.</p>\u000a<p>It is both exhilarating and terrifying that term is starting again, and that I&#8217;m going to be a senior.  I&#8217;ve survived three years at MIT so far!  (And, with luck, I&#8217;ll still have two more to go).  Crazy.</p>
