V<p>While I was visiting home, I spent quite a while playing with my mom&#8217;s 7D.  Here are some of the fruits of my efforts!  These photos, of the potted flowers on our deck, were taken in the gorgeous morning sunlight the morning I left.  I especially love the effect of the dew in some of these.</p>\u000a<p>Any and all post-processing was done by my mom, Virginia Hamrick (hence the copyright).</p>\u000a<p><a href="http://jhamrick.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/p359477909-4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-218" title="p359477909-4" src="http://jhamrick.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/p359477909-4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="516" /></a></p>\u000a<p><a href="http://jhamrick.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/p307436560-3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-217" title="p307436560-3" src="http://jhamrick.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/p307436560-3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="388" /></a></p>\u000a<p><a href="http://jhamrick.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/p261000253-3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-216" title="p261000253-3" src="http://jhamrick.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/p261000253-3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="405" /></a></p>\u000a<p><a href="http://jhamrick.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/p244603875-2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-215" title="p244603875-2" src="http://jhamrick.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/p244603875-2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="252" /></a><a href="http://jhamrick.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/p102391045-4.jpg"></a></p>\u000a<p><a href="http://jhamrick.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/p102391045-4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-214" title="p102391045-4" src="http://jhamrick.mit.edu/wp-content/uploads/2010/06/p102391045-4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="439" /></a></p>
